        public static long milliseconds(String isoDateTime)
                         throws ParseException
        Obtains a time to the current system millisecond time using ISO 8601 in the specified time zone.
        Parameters:
        isoDateTime - this date-time as a String, such as 2019-06-16T10:15:30Z or 2019-06-16T10:15:30+01:00[Europe/Paris].
        Returns:
        the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT for the date and time specified by the arguments.
        Throws:
        ParseException - If isoDateTime format is invalid
